  "text": "Recent work [CITATION_1] has shown that proteins have a significant effect on the corrosion rate of Co-Cr-Mo implants. The presence of proteins in the abrasive test slurry can affect the cathodic kinetics. The protein enhanced interaction is interpreted in terms of its effect in the particle entrainment process.",
